                    <lb n="4"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπ</supplied>όλλ<supplied reason="lost">ωνι</supplied></name></persName> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> à Apollon <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> to Apollo <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> ad Apollo <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>The only word that may be isolated is the name of Apollo, presumably at the dative case, which implies that the inscription is a dedication and probably 
               ended with that word.</p>
